headline: Intel’s Granite Rapids processor seeing "meaningful ramp," KeyBanc analysts say
summary: Investing.com - Intel’s (NASDAQ:INTC) server processor deployments on cloud platforms grew at a steady pace in August, as the semiconductor group was bolstered by a "meaningful ramp" in its latest-generation processor, according to analysts at KeyBanc Capital Markets.

headline: Intel (INTC): Evaluating Valuation Following Government Stake, Fresh Funding, and Leadership Overhaul
summary: If you have been following Intel (INTC) lately, you have probably noticed the stock has been caught in the crosshairs of several major headlines. The US government’s $8.9 billion equity stake and additional financing from SoftBank have set the stage for a high-stakes turnaround. But it is not just about fresh capital. With a wave of new senior executive appointments, Intel is racing to reinforce its core business, drive innovation in its foundry unit, and signal a new direction to investors...
